Now I can see the issue! On line 98, the code calls `node.firstChildNode.elementType` without checking if `node.firstChildNode` is null. The problem occurs when there's an empty THEN block in the malformed code:

```kotlin
if ("a" == "b") {
} else if ("b" == "c") else {
}
```

In this case, the THEN node has no first child node (it's empty), causing the NullPointerException.

Let me also check the test files to understand the expected behavior better:

